cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

This paper deals with security and privacy issues in SGX, which is a hardware-based security feature for Intel processors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves designing and implementing attack techniques, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses cache monitoring techniques, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and detecting specific sequences, which is related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
